        hey what's up everyone, just wanted to say hi to my 1D little brothers *everyone bear with me, the billboard hot 100 page was a fun place to chat years ago with dozens of music fans from all over the world, incl. the artists themselves*

        harry: congrats lil' bro!! check you out selling out madison square garden & having a #1 smash on the hot 100 chart!! couldn't be more proud and happy for you! i LOVE 'adore you', 'late night talking' & 'daydreaming'. reminds me of when usher, michael jackson, tlc, whitney houston, justin timberlake & mariah carey dominated the #1 spot & never left the top 10...great job! *applause* & see, you're re-inventing your look & sound and still just being yourself. justin was the exact same way ;) you're still mine btw LOL!

        niall: fantastic job getting a #1 & top 10 album here in america! i know it was you i chatted with on the hot 100 page years ago ;))) also, i went on your twitter page recently and GREAT JOB keeping the public focused on your career and not on your personal life. *huge applause* you're following justin timberlake's personal example perfectly!! that's all i was trying to say to you guys, i don't know him personally but he never had any drama with the fans, even when nsync first burst onto the u.s. music scene. not 1 time! today he's a lil' more open with his personal business, but perfectly balanced his private & public life his whole career esp. during the nsync days. you remind me so much of him back then :))))) oh he also loves to play golf, maybe you 2 could do a golf charity event? ;)))

        zayn: glad to see you're more reserved on your twitter page, that's all i was trying to say back on billboard years ago. the public should only be focused on you all as a group, nothing more. but you have to set the boundaries on what you want the public to know about you....see what a complete waste of time all that fighting was? that's exactly what justin timberlake did, he kept his personal life out of the spotlight. but moving on, just wanted to wish you the best and pls. reach out to people like elton john & paul mccartney if you ever need any advice. also don't worry about the hit records, they can always come back ;).

        louis & liam: louis congrats on selling out shows! and i agree with you, 1D has a lot to be proud of, but if i ever had the chance to speak with modest management, i would have some choice critiques *friendly though* for them. you all were young kids *both groups* and modest management should've been able to see the forest thru the trees *what we say here in america*. liam: can't wait to hear more new music from you! i have lots of great memories seeing my 5 lil' brothers on billboard...midnight memories is my very fave album by you guys, still sounds great after all these years. much love to you all! still my lil' bros, that hasn't changed ;)))))
